Description: Gold Institute actively engages in the discussion of national security issues
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The security interests of the United States and Canada, the nations of Europe have a great deal in common. Yet there is little coherent thinking and action, outside a few organs of government on each side of the Atlantic, to address larger, longer-term, emerging security issues that equally affect those on both sides of the ocean. From strict national security issues such as nuclear proliferation, terrorism, cyber security and the increased instability in regions bordering Europe, to the more complex security - economic issues of energy, industrial and information economics, foods and international commerce, all the way to the exceptionally complex issues of emigration and healthcare, the issues we all face grow ever more difficult and tightly integrated. The purpose of the Gold Institute is to actively engage in the discussion of these issues by those who have not only thought deeply about them, but who have actively participated in efforts to affect them. By providing both coherent thoughts, and recommended actions to address various issues, the Gold Institute aims to bring real solutions to real problems in real time.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: The XMPP Standards Foundation (XSF) is an independent, nonprofit standards development organization which defines open protocols for presence, instant messaging, and real-time communication and collaboration on top of the IETF’s Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol (XMPP).  The foundation provides information and infrastructure to the worldwide community on Jabber and XMPP developers, service providers, and end users. It publishes extensions to the core protocols in the form of XMPP Extension Protocols (XEPs). The foundation offers free individual memberships based on technical merit. New members apply for membership and are elected by the existing members if they are active participants in the XMPP developer community through authoring or commenting on XMPP protocols, implementing XMPP-based software, offering XMPP-based services, and more. It also offers various active discussion venues for Jabber and XMPP developers, system administrators, and end users. The XMPP Standards Foundation receives sponsors from several organizations, including Coversant, Erlang Solutions, KOLON BENIT, US Secure Hosting Center, Genesys | Angel, ProcessOne, and Voxeo. Professional XMPP Programming with JavaScript and jQuery , Programming Jabber, and Instant Messaging in Java are some of the books published by the foundation. The XMPP Standards Foundation was founded in 2001.

Description: GayRealEstate.com started with one incident in the early 1990's.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: GayRealEstate.com started with one incident in the early 1990's: an instance of "quiet homophobia" occurred while I was working at a Re/Max office. A gay couple interested in buying a home stopped in the office and were assisted by the floor agent. A floor agent is an agent that is essentially "on-duty" and gets to handle all of the incoming calls and walk-in traffic; it's an opportunity to pick up new clients. Generally, the floor agent is never the best agent in the office. This is because all of the great agents are busy with clients and don't have time to take floor duty. On this particular day, the floor agent was a straight friend of mine who had probably never met an openly gay person. After he met with the couple and they left, the agent took a lot of ribbing about working with these new clients. While he went on to find these guys a home, I questioned how well they were represented.

Description: East West College of Natural Medicine is a school in Sarasota.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The East West College of Natural Medicine in Sarasota, Florida, strives to be the nation’s leading provider in Oriental Medicine education by promoting the advancement of integrative health care through its outstanding program. The school welcomes all students with an interest in acupuncture and Oriental Medicine. To apply, you must be at least 18 years old, have earned a high school diploma and completed two years of undergraduate coursework in the humanities, social sciences, English and mathematics and science. Admissions also require you to submit a personal essay. The college offers academics through its simultaneous dual degree program. Students can earn a bachelor’s of professional health sciences and master’s of science in Oriental Medicine concurrently when they complete the program. Coursework covers virtually all aspects of Oriental Medicine, from acupuncture science to herbal sciences. Just minutes from the campus is the Siesta Key beach, recognized as one of America’s best beaches. Living in Sarasota, students also have opportunities for environmentally conscious activities, including Pilates and yoga classes and numerous health food stores in the downtown district. The arts and culture scene of Sarasota also provides students with great student life resources. Outside of class you can enjoy the Sarasota Film Festival, Asolo Theatre Company productions, Florida Studio Theatre and Sarasota Ballet of Florida, just to name a few. To be considered for financial aid, students must complete a FAFSA. Forms of tuition assistance include the Florida Bright Futures Scholarship program, Florida Student Assistant grant, federal loans and the Jose Marti scholarship.
